From Subject Re freely distributable public key cryptography c code where Victor Iseli wrote Numerical Recipes in C has a nice section on encryption and decryption based on the DES There is also source code provided I think some versions of this book are distributed with the source code on disk the source code can also be ordered from the publisher Victor Iseli Yes I benchmarked the DES implementation in the Recipes in C it is about orders of magnitude SLOWER than the Outerbridge Karn Gillogly et al It may be instructional but it isn't very AD FC AC